==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Ern
<hw>Ern</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <ety>[Cf.
<er>Erme</er>.]</ety> <def>To stir with strong emotion; to grieve; to
mourn. <note>[Corrupted into <xex>yearn</xex> in modern editions of
Shakespeare.]</note></def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Ernest</ent>⟦br⟧
